lidarity trial' to jumpstart search for COVID-19 treatment |url=https://news.un.org/en/story/2020/03/1059722 |publisher=United Nations, World Health Organization |accessdate=2 April 2020 |language=en |date=18 March 2020 |archive-date=2020-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323101633/https://news.un.org/en/story/2020/03/1059722 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="kai">{{cite news |last1=Kupferschmidt |first1=Kai |last2=Cohen |first2=Jon |title=WHO launches global megatrial of the four most promising coronavirus treatments |url=https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2020/03/who-launches-global-megatrial-four-most-promising-coronavirus-treatments |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=Science |publisher=AAAS |date=22 March 2020 |language=en |archive-date=2020-03-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322232707/https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2020/03/who-launches-global-megatrial-four-most-promising-coronavirus-treatments |dead-url=no }}</ref>。试验于2020年3月18日被宣布<ref name="who"/>，截至4月21日，已有100多个国家参加<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019/global-research-on-novel-coronavirus-2019-ncov/solidarity-clinical-trial-for-covid-19-treatments|title='Solidarity' clinical trial for COVID-19 treatment|last=|first=|date=|website=www.who.int|publisher=World Health Organization|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200430081829/https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019/global-research-on-novel-coronavirus-2019-ncov/solidarity-clinical-trial-for-covid-19-treatments|archive-date=2020-04-30|access-date=2020-04-22|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 國家和政府間實驗室 ===
美國能源部的聯邦科學實驗室，例如[[橡樹嶺國家實驗室|橡樹嶺國家實驗室]]（Oak Ridge National Laboratory，ORNL），已經關閉了所有訪客和許多員工的大門，並且如果可能的話，非必需的人員和科學家也必須在家工作。 強烈建議承包商在必要時隔離其設施和人員。 ORNL的整體運作仍不受影響<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ornl.gov/content/covid-19-advisory|title=COVID-19 Advisory | ORNL|website=ornl.gov|access-date=2020-03-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326122304/https://www.ornl.gov/content/covid-19-advisory|archive-date=2020-03-26|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[勞倫斯利佛摩國家實驗室|勞倫斯利佛摩國家實驗室]]（Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory，LLNL）受[[白宫冠状病毒工作组|白宫COVID-19工作组]]的委託，利用其大部分超級計算能力進一步研究病毒流，可能的突變和其他因素。 同時暫時減少其他項目或無限期地延遲它們<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.llnl.gov/news/lab-antibody-anti-viral-research-aids-covid-19-response|title=Lab antibody, anti-viral research aids COVID-19 response | Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory|website=llnl.gov|access-date=2020-03-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326122613/https://www.llnl.gov/news/lab-antibody-anti-viral-research-aids-covid-19-response|archive-date=2020-03-26|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[歐洲分子生物學實驗室|歐洲分子生物學實驗室]](EMBL)已經關閉了歐洲的所有六個地點（巴塞羅那，格勒諾布爾，漢堡，海德堡，欣克斯頓，和羅馬）。 EMBL的所有東道國政府都對COVID-19採取了嚴格的控制措施。 已指示EMBL工作人員遵循當地政府的建議。 已授權少量工作人員到場提供基本服務，例如動物設施維護或數據服務。 已指示所有其他工作人員留在家裡。 EMBL還取消了訪問人員對現場的所有訪問。這包括實際參加在海德堡的“課程和會議”計劃，EMBL-EBI培訓課程，以及所有站點的所有其他研討會，課程和公眾訪問。 同時，[[欧洲生物信息研究所|欧洲生物信息研究所]]正在創建用於數據/信息交換的歐洲COVID-19數據平台。 目標是收集和共享快速可用的研究數據，以實現協同作用，交叉應用和使用具有不同程度的匯總，驗證和/或完整性的各種數據集。 該平台包括兩個相互連接的組件：SARS-CoV-2數據中心，可組織SARS-CoV-2暴發序列數據流，並為歐洲和全球研究社區提供全面的開放數據共享；以及一個更廣泛的COVID- 19門戶网站<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.embl.org/news/lab-matters/corona-updates/|title=EMBL's response to the coronavirus outbreak|accessdate=2020-08-01|archive-date=2020-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200410164757/https://www.embl.org/news/lab-matters/corona-updates/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.embl.org/news/science/embl-ebi-leads-international-collaboration-to-share-covid-19-research-data/?_ga=2.135566577.1552695299.1585763730-859685221.1575360586|title=EMBL-EBI leads International collaboration to share COVID-19 research data|accessdate=2020-08-01|archive-date=2020-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200410164759/https://www.embl.org/news/science/embl-ebi-leads-international-collaboration-to-share-covid-19-research-data/?_ga=2.135566577.1552695299.1585763730-859685221.1575360586|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ena/pathogens/covid-19|title=EMBL-EBI COVID-19 Data Platform|accessdate=2020-08-01|archive-date=2020-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200410164803/https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ena/pathogens/covid-19|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

=== 世界气象组织 ===

[[世界气象组织|世界气象组织]]表达了他们对于观测系统的顾虑。{{link-en|飞行气象数据中续项目|Aircraft Meteorological Data Relay}}使用从43个航空的舰队所得出的飞行数据，而其观测根据不同区域被降低了50%到80%。尽管世界气象组织表达了维修和维护可能被影响的担忧，其他自动系统的数据都基本没有被影响。大部分[[发达国家|发达国家]]的手动观测数量也有很大的下滑。<ref>{{cite press release|title=WMO is concerned about impact of COVID-19 on observing system|url=https://public.wmo.int/en/media/press-release/wmo-concerned-about-impact-of-covid-19-observing-system|publisher=World Meteorological Organization|date=31 March 2020|language=en|access-date=2020-08-09|archive-date=2020-05-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200504104733/https://public.wmo.int/en/media/press-release/wmo-concerned-about-impact-of-covid-19-observing-system|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 開放科學 ===
加快[[開放科學|開放科學]]研究的需要使得多個民間社會組織創建了"開放COVID承諾"(Open COVID Pledge)<ref>{{Cite web|title=Open COVID Pledge: Removing Obstacles to Sharing IP in the Fight Against COVID-19|url=https://creativecommons.org/2020/04/07/open-covid-pledge-removing-obstacles-to-sharing-ip-in-the-fight-against-covid-19/|date=2020-04-07|website=Creative Commons|language=en-US|access-date=2020-05-04|archive-date=2020-05-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200501232545/https://creativecommons.org/2020/04/07/open-covid-pledge-removing-obstacles-to-sharing-ip-in-the-fight-against-covid-19/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=PIJIP Among Founding Partners of Open COVID Pledge|url=https://www.wcl.american.edu/impact/initiatives-programs/pijip/news/pijip-among-founding-partners-of-open-covid-pledge/|website=American University Washington College of Law|language=en|access-date=2020-05-04|archive-date=2020-05-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200520101022/https://www.wcl.american.edu/impact/initiatives-programs/pijip/news/pijip-among-founding-partners-of-open-covid-pledge/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，要求不同行業在大流行期間釋放其知識產權，以幫助找到治愈這種疾病的方法。 幾家科技巨頭加入了這一承諾<ref>{{Cite web|title=Tech Giants Join the CC-Supported Open COVID Pledge|url=https://creativecommons.org/2020/04/20/tech-giants-join-the-cc-supported-open-covid-pledge/|date=2020-04-20|website=Creative Commons|language=en-US|access-date=2020-05-04|archive-date=2020-05-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200501232704/https://creativecommons.org/2020/04/20/tech-giants-join-the-cc-supported-open-covid-pledge/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。 承諾包括發布Open COVID許可證<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Open COVID Pledge|url=https://opencovidpledge.org/|website=opencovidpledge.org|language=en-US|access-date=2020-05-04|archive-date=2020-05-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200502080338/https://opencovidpledge.org/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。 長期以來一直倡導開放獲取的組織，例如[[知識共享|知識共享]]組織(Creative Commons)，進行了無數呼籲和行動，以促進科學中的開放獲取，將其作為抗擊該疾病的關鍵要素<ref>{{Cite web|title=Creative Commons' Response to COVID-19|url=https://creativecommons.org/creative-commons-response-to-covid-19/|website=Creative Commons|language=en-US|access-date=2020-05-04|archive-date=2020-05-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200502083845/https://creativecommons.org/creative-commons-response-to-covid-19/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=La risposta di Creative Commons all’emergenza causata dal COVID-19: interventi a tutela del personale e della comunità. – Italia|url=https://creativecommons.it/chapterIT/index.php/1035/|language=en-US|access-date=2020-05-04|archive-date=2020-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200709054335/https://creativecommons.it/chapterIT/index.php/1035/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。 其中包括公開呼籲採取更加開放的政策<ref>{{Cite web|title=Now Is the Time for Open Access Policies—Here’s Why|url=https://creativecommons.org/2020/03/19/now-is-the-time-for-open-access-policies-heres-why/|date=2020-03-19|website=Creative Commons|language=en-US|access-date=2020-05-04|archive-date=2020-05-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200501232525/https://creativecommons.org/2020/03/19/now-is-the-time-for-open-access-policies-heres-why/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，呼籲科學家對出版物採取零禁運期限，對文章實施[[知识共享许可协议|知识共享许可协议(CC BY)]]，並對研究數據實施CC0豁免<ref>{{Cite web|title=Dr. Lucie Guibault on What Scientists Should Know About Open Access|url=https://creativecommons.org/2020/03/27/what-scientists-should-know-about-open-access/|date=2020-03-27|website=Creative Commons|language=en-US|access-date=2020-05-04|archive-date=2020-05-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200510050924/https://creativecommons.org/2020/03/27/what-scientists-should-know-about-open-access/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 。 其他組織質疑當前的科學文化，呼籲建立更開放的公共科學<ref>{{Cite web|title=Antivírus 02 – Que ciência queremos? - ANTIVÍRUS|url=https://open.spotify.com/episode/1XzfApJbww4f5rI5W1QdfJ|website=Spotify|language=en|access-date=2020-05-04|archive-date=2020-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200709054324/https://open.spotify.com/episode/1XzfApJbww4f5rI5W1QdfJ|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

對于COVID-19的研究和信息，這些信息可以幫助通過[[開放科學|開放科學]]實現[[公民科學|公民科學]]，可通過其他[[開放獲取|開放獲取]]和開放科學網站獲得更多在線資源，包括[[劍橋大學出版社|劍橋大學出版社]]<ref name=CUP_1>{{cite web| title=Coronavirus Free Access Collection| url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/browse-subjects/medicine/coronavirus-free-access-collection| publisher=[[Cambridge_University_Press|Cambridge University Press]]| date=2020| access-date=4 April 2020| archive-date=2020-08-02| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200802122847/https://www.cambridge.org/core/browse-subjects/medicine/coronavirus-free-access-collection| dead-url=no}}</ref>，[[学术出版与学术资源联盟|学术出版与学术资源联盟]]<ref name=SPARC_1>{{cite web| title=The Coronavirus and Open Science: Our reads and Open use cases| url=https://sparceurope.org/coronaopensciencereadsandusecases| publisher=[[Scholarly_Publishing_and_Academic_Resources_Coalition|Scholarly Publishing and Academic Resources Coalition]] Europe| date=March 2020| access-date=4 April 2020| archive-date=2020-08-03| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803112939/https://sparceurope.org/coronaopensciencereadsandusecases/| dead-url=no}}</ref>，《[[柳葉刀_(雜誌)|柳葉刀]]》<ref name=TL_1>{{cite web| title=The Lancet COVID-19 Resource Centre| url=https://www.thelancet.com/coronavirus| publisher=[[Elsevier|Elsevier]] Inc.| date=April 2020| access-date=4 April 2020| archive-date=2020-02-23| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223104640/https://www.thelancet.com/coronavirus| dead-url=no}}</ref>，[[約翰威立|約翰威立]]<ref name=Wil_1>{{cite web| title=Covid-19: Novel Coronavirus Outbreak| url=https://novel-coronavirus.onlinelibrary.wiley.com| publisher=[[John_Wiley_&_Sons|John Wiley & Sons]], Inc.| date=March 2020| access-date=4 April 2020| archive-date=2020-09-24| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200924195411/https://novel-coronavirus.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/| dead-url=no}}</ref>，和[[施普林格·自然|施普林格·自然]]<ref name=Spri_1>{{cite web| title=SARS-CoV-2 and COVID-19| url=https://www.springernature.com/gp/researchers/campaigns/coronavirus| publisher=[[Springer_Nature|Springer Nature]]| date=2020| access-date=4 April 2020| archive-date=2020-08-02| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200802034626/https://www.springernature.com/gp/researchers/campaigns/coronavirus| dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 計算研究與公民科學 ==

2020年3月，[[美國能源部|美國能源部]]，[[美國國家科學基金會|美國國家科學基金會]]，[[美國國家航空航天局|美國國家航空航天局]]，工業界和9所大學匯集了資源來訪問[[IBM|IBM]]的超級計算機，並結合了[[慧與科技|慧與科技]]，[[亞馬遜公司|亞馬遜]]，[[微軟|微軟]]和[[谷歌|谷歌]]的雲計算資源來進行藥物發現 <ref name="Summit">{{cite news |last1=Shankland |first1=Stephen |title=Sixteen supercomputers tackle coronavirus cures in the US |url=https://www.cnet.com/news/sixteen-supercomputers-tackle-coronavirus-cures-in-us/ |date=2020-03-23 |accessdate=27 April 2020 |work=CNET |publisher=ViacomCBS |archive-date=2020-07-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200726032743/https://www.cnet.com/news/sixteen-supercomputers-tackle-coronavirus-cures-in-us/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="C-19HPCC">{{cite web|url=https://covid19-hpc-consortium.org/|title=The COVID-19 High Performance Computing Consortium|publisher=The COVID-19 High Performance Computing Consortium|date=2020|accessdate=2020-04-27|archive-date=2020-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200427000406/https://covid19-hpc-consortium.org/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。 COVID‑19高性能計算聯盟還旨在預測疾病蔓延，為可能的疫苗建模，並篩選成千上萬種化合物，以設計COVID‑19疫苗或療法<ref name="Summit"/><ref name="C-19HPCC"/>。

2020年3月，[[分佈式計算|分佈式計算]]項目[[Folding@home|Folding@home]]發起了一個項目，以協助全球醫學研究人員。 項目的最初一波旨在模擬SARS-CoV-2病毒和相關SARS-CoV病毒的潛在蛋白靶標，該蛋白先前已經被研究過<ref name="tomshw-fah">{{cite web |last1=Broekhuijsen |first1=Niels |title=Help Cure Coronavirus with Your PC's Leftover Processing Power |url=https://www.tomshardware.com/news/folding-fight-coronavirus |website=Tom's Hardware |accessdate=12 March 2020 |date=3 March 2020 |archive-date=2020-08-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200821001025/https://www.tomshardware.com/news/folding-fight-coronavirus |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="fah-newspost">{{cite web |last1=Bowman |first1=Greg |title=Folding@home takes up the fight against COVID-19 / 2019-nCoV |url=https://foldingathome.org/2020/02/27/foldinghome-takes-up-the-fight-against-covid-19-2019-ncov/ |website=Folding@home |accessdate=12 March 2020 |date=27 February 2020 |archive-date=2020-03-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315194201/https://foldingathome.org/2020/02/27/foldinghome-takes-up-the-fight-against-covid-19-2019-ncov/ |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.hpcwire.com/2020/03/16/foldinghome-turns-its-massive-crowdsourced-computer-network-against-covid-19/|title = Folding@home Turns Its Massive Crowdsourced Computer Network Against COVID-19|date = March 16, 2020|accessdate = 2020-08-01|archive-date = 2020-08-06|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200806090436/https://www.hpcwire.com/2020/03/16/foldinghome-turns-its-massive-crowdsourced-computer-network-against-covid-19/|dead-url = no}}</ref>。

2020年5月，[[斯克里普斯研究所|斯克里普斯研究所]](Scripps Research)和IBM的[[世界公共网格|世界公共网格(World Community Grid)]]之間建立了OpenPandemics-COVID-19合作關係。 該合作夥伴關係是一個分佈式計算項目，“將在[連接的家用PC]的背景下自動運行模擬實驗，這將有助於預測特定化合物作為COVID-19的可能療法的有效性”<ref name=WCG_1>{{cite web| title=OpenPandemics - COVID-19| url=https://www.worldcommunitygrid.org/research/opn1/overview.do| publisher=IBM| date=2020| access-date=18 May 2020| archive-date=2020-07-29| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200729185215/https://www.worldcommunitygrid.org/research/opn1/overview.do| dead-url=no}}</ref>。

Covid Near You流行病學工具“使用眾包數據對地圖進行可視化處理，以幫助公民和公共衛生機構識別近期和潛在的大流行冠狀病毒COVID-19熱點。”

